  "prompt": "What are the vacations in IITs?",
  "response": "The Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs) generally follow a similar academic calendar, but there might be slight variations between different IITs. Here's a typical vacation schedule:\n\n1. Summer Vacation\n- Duration: Approximately 2-2.5 months\n- Usually from early May to late July\n- Longest break of the academic year\n\n2. Winter Vacation\n- Duration: Around 3-4 weeks\n- Typically from mid-December to mid-January\n- Includes Christmas and New Year holidays\n\n3. Other Short Breaks\n- Semester breaks between Fall and Spring semesters\n- Diwali holidays (usually 3-5 days)\n- Holi holidays (usually 2-3 days)\n- Independence Day and Republic Day breaks\n\n4. Mid-Semester Breaks\n- Short breaks between semesters\n- Usually 1-2 weeks long\n\n5. Regional/Local Holidays\n- Each IIT might have additional local holidays based on regional festivals\n\nNote: Exact dates and duration can vary slightly between different IIT campuses. Students should always refer to their specific institute's academic calendar for precise vacation schedules.",
